Package: fixer
Architecture: any
Depends:
 ${misc:Depends},
 ${shlibs:Depends},
 systemd
Recommends:
 linux-perf,
 bpftrace,
 cargo,
 nodejs,
 npm,
 python3-pip,
 postgresql-client
Description: local evidence engine for Linux maintenance opportunities
 Fixer inventories what is actually running on a Linux machine, watches
 configured repositories, ingests crashes and warnings, ranks fix
 opportunities, and can hand bounded evidence bundles to Codex for
 patch proposals.
 .
 The package installs both the command-line client and the systemd
 service, along with a default configuration file under /etc/fixer.

Package: fixer-server
Architecture: any
Depends:
 ${misc:Depends},
 ${shlibs:Depends},
 systemd
Recommends:
 postgresql,
 caddy
Breaks:
 fixer (<< 0.9.0-1)
Replaces:
 fixer (<< 0.9.0-1)
Description: standalone Fixer aggregation server
 fixer-server accepts opted-in Fixer submissions, clusters repeated
 findings, manages quarantine and worker leases, and serves a small
 landing page plus JSON API.
 .
 The package is configured to work immediately on a local Debian host:
 it binds to 127.0.0.1:8080 and stores server state in a local SQLite
 database under /var/lib/fixer-server. Public deployments can switch to
 PostgreSQL by setting FIXER_SERVER_POSTGRES_URL in
 /etc/fixer/fixer-server.env.
